'''Diego Nicolás de la Cruz Arcosa''' (born 1 June 1997) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a central midfielder for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Serie A]] club [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|418994}}</ref>

==Club career==
===River Plate===
On 15 August 2017, de la Cruz joined Argentinian club [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 August 2017 |title=Nicolás de la Cruz se sumó a River Plate |url=http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/nicolas-de-la-cruz-se-sumo-a-river-plate |access-date=20 April 2023 |website=caRiverPlate.com.ar |language=es-AR}}</ref>

===Flamengo===
On 24 December 2023, it was announced that de la Cruz would join Brazilian club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] at the start of the [[2024 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|2024 season]], signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 December 2023 |title=De La Cruz é presente de Natal para a Nação |url=https://www.flamengo.com.br/noticias/futebol/de-la-cruz-e-presente-de-natal-para-a-nacao |access-date=2 January 2024 |website=Flamengo |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=24 December 2023 |title=Flamengo anuncia contratação de De La Cruz como presente de Natal: "Nação, tamo junto" |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/2023/12/24/flamengo-anuncia-de-la-cruz-como-presente-de-natal.ghtml |access-date=2 January 2024 |website=ge |language=pt-br}}</ref>

==International career==
De la Cruz began his international career for Uruguay with [[Uruguay national under-17 football team|under-17 team]].<ref name="auf1">{{cite web|title=11 - Nicolás De La Cruz - AUF|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/11-nicol-aacute-s-de-la-cruz-2017/|accessdate=10 October 2020}}</ref> He was captain of [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay under-20 team]] which won the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]] and reached the semi-finals of the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref name="auf2">{{cite web|title=Sudamericano Sub-20 2017|url=https://auf.org.uy/sudamericano-sub-20-2017/|accessdate=10 October 2020}}</ref>

On 18 September 2020, de la Cruz was included in Uruguay's 26-man preliminary squad for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifying]] matches against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref name="auf3">{{cite web|title=26 futbolistas reservados del exterior para el debut en las Eliminatorias|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/26-futbolistas-reservados-del-exterior-para-el-debut-en-las-eliminatorias/|accessdate=10 October 2020}}</ref> He was later included in the final squad and made his senior debut on 8 October 2020 in Uruguay's 2–1 win against Chile. He started the match and played 55 minutes before getting replaced by [[Nahitan Nández]].<ref name="auf4">{{cite web|title=Uruguay venció 2-1 a Chile en el estadio Centenario|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/detalles-uruguay-chile-fecha-1-eliminatorias-2022/|accessdate=10 October 2020}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, de la Cruz was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
De la Cruz is the half-brother of former Uruguayan international footballer [[Carlos Sánchez (Uruguayan footballer)|Carlos Sánchez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/america/deportes/el-uruguayo-nicolas-de-la-cruz-hermano-carlos-sanchez-ficha-por-river/20000010-3352831|title=El uruguayo Nicolás de la Cruz, hermano de Carlos Sánchez, ficha por River|trans-title=Uruguayan Nicolás de la Cruz, brother of Carlos Sánchez, signs for River|publisher=EFE|language=es|date=16 August 2017|access-date=10 October 2020}}</ref> Their nephew [[Facundo Trinidad]] is also a professional footballer. All three of them are youth academy graduates of [[Liverpool F.C. (Montevideo)|Liverpool Montevideo]].<ref name="sobrino">{{cite web|title=Facundo Trinidad firmó contrato|url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com.uy/noticias/facundo-trinidad-firmo-contrato|accessdate=10 October 2020}}</ref>

